#. type: Title #
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_patient_population.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Patient Population"
msgstr "Patsientide populatsioon"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_patient_population.Rmd:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "As the process, although supported by various tools, relies on the collection, interpretation and monitoring of information by qualified professionals, NeoIPC surveillance is currently being targeted at the most common nosocomial infections in high-risk neonates, in order to make it sustainable in a continuous manner in as many settings as possible. This means that patients with a birth weight below 1500 g and/or a gestational age below 32 weeks at the time of birth are included into the surveillance database if they are admitted to a participating neonatology department within the first 120 days of life. In combination with the filter settings specified above, this results in the composition of the patient population shown in @fig-bw and @fig-ga.\n"
msgstr "Kuna protsess, kuigi seda toetavad mitmesugused vahendid, tugineb kvalifitseeritud spetsialistide poolt kogutud, tõlgendatud ja jälgitud teabele, on NeoIPC seire praegu suunatud kõige levinumatele haiglanakkustele kõrge riskiga vastsündinutel, et tagada selle jätkusuutlikkus võimalikult paljudes keskkondades. See tähendab, et patsiendid, kelle sünnikaal on alla 1500 g ja/või gestatsiooniga alla 32 nädala sünnihetkel, lisatakse järelevalve andmebaasi, kui nad on sünnijärgselt esimese 120 päeva jooksul võetud osalevasse neonatoloogiaosakonda. Koos eespool nimetatud filtri seadetega annab see tulemuseks patsientide populatsiooni koosseisu, mis on näidatud @fig-bw ja @fig-ga.\n"

#. type: Title #
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_nosocomial_infections.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Nosocomial Infections"
msgstr "Haiglanakkused"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_nosocomial_infections.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Nosocomial infections represent the primary endpoint of NeoIPC surveillance. In @tbl-incidence-density-rates, the incidence densities of sepsis/BSI, pneumonia and necrotising enterocolitis, as well as the combined endpoint 'severe infection', are displayed. Overall `r dR$numberOfSevereInfections` severe infections were recorded in `r dR$numberOfPatients` infants resulting in an average number of `r dR$averageSevereInfectionsPerPatient` infections per patient.\n"
msgstr "Haiglanakkused on NeoIPC seire peamine lõpptulemus. @tbl-incidence-density-rates on esitatud sepsise/BSI, kopsupõletiku ja nekrotiseeriva enterokoliidi esinemissagedus ning kombineeritud lõpptulemus „raske nakkus”. Kokku registreeriti `r dR$numberOfSevereInfections` imikul `r dR$numberOfPatients` rasket nakkust, mis teeb keskmiselt `r dR$averageSevereInfectionsPerPatient` nakkust patsiendi kohta.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_nosocomial_infections.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Device-associated infections can be found in @tbl-device-associated-incidence-density-rates.\n"
msgstr "Seadmetega seotud infektsioonid on esitatud @tbl-device-associated-incidence-density-rates.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_infectious_agents.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Infectious Agents"
msgstr "Nakkusetekitajad"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_infectious_agents.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Epidemiology of the infectious agents causing nosocomial infections in neonatology is complex and there is a lot of potential for bias. While low diagnostic sensitivity (low blood volume) and specificity (contamination) are a general problem in the neonatal population, the lack of availability of some or all means of microbiological diagnostics, or the lack of financial resources can have a strong effect on the detection rates in resource-constrained settings.\n"
msgstr "Neonatoloogias haiglanakkusi põhjustavate nakkusetekitajate epidemioloogia on keeruline ja sisaldab palju potentsiaalset eelarvamust. Kuigi madal diagnostiline tundlikkus (madal vere maht) ja spetsiifilisus (saastumine) on üldine probleem vastsündinute populatsioonis, võib mõnede või kõigi mikrobioloogiliste diagnostikavahendite kättesaamatus või rahaliste vahendite puudus mõjutada tugevalt avastamismäära ressursipiirangutega keskkondades.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_infectious_agents.Rmd:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "<!-- When comparing data with the information on pathogens presented in @tbl-agent-per-infection-rate and information on drug resistance in @tbl-abr-infection-rate, please also have a look at the infectious agent detection rates presented in @tbl-infectious-agent-detection-rate and the antibiotic resistance test rates in @tbl-resistance-test-rate. -->\n"
msgstr "<!-- Kui võrdlete andmeid @tbl-agent-per-infection-rate esitatud patogeenide teabe ja @tbl-abr-infection-rate esitatud ravimresistentsuse teabega, vaadake ka @tbl-infectious-agent-detection-rate esitatud nakkusetekitajate avastamise määra ja @tbl-resistance-test-rate esitatud antibiootikumiresistentsuse testide määra. -->\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_infectious_agents.Rmd:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "In total, `r dR$numberOfInfectiousAgents` infectious agents were detected in the `r dR$numberOfInfectionsWithAgent` infections that were reported to have yielded at least one agent from either the primary infection and/or the secondary bloodstream infection resulting from it (@tbl-agent-per-infection-rate). These `r dR$numberOfInfectionsWithAgent` diagnostic-positive infections out of `r dR$overallNumberOfInfections` overall infections represent an Infectious Agent Detection Rate of `r dR$infectiousAgentDetectionRate` per 100 infections (@tbl-infectious-agent-detection-rate).\n"
msgstr "Kokku tuvastati 335 nakkusetekitajat 288 nakkusjuhtumi puhul, mille puhul teatati vähemalt ühe nakkusetekitaja esinemisest esmase nakkuse ja/või sellest tuleneva teisese vereringe nakkuse korral (@tbl-agent-per-infection-rate). Need 288 diagnoosipositiivset nakkusjuhtu 685 nakkusjuhtumi koguarvust tähendavad nakkusetekitajate avastamismäära 42,0 100 nakkusjuhtumi kohta (@tbl-infectious-agent-detection-rate).\n"

#. type: Title #
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_risk_and_protective_factors.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Risk and Protective Factors"
msgstr "Riskitegurid ja kaitsvad tegurid"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_risk_and_protective_factors.Rmd:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next to the inherent risk factors gestational age and birth weight there are also a number of expositional factors that influence the risk of an infant to acquire a multi-drug-resistant pathogen or to develop an infection. @tbl-risk-density-rates shows the presence of these factors in the NeoIPC Surveillance population.\n"
msgstr "Lisaks loomulikele riskiteguritele, nagu raseduse kestus ja sünnikaal, on ka mitmeid ekspositsioonitegureid, mis mõjutavad imiku riski nakatuda mitme ravimi suhtes resistentse patogeeniga või haigestuda infektsiooni. @tbl-risk-density-rates on näidatud nende tegurite esinemine NeoIPC järelevalve populatsioonis.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_surgery.Rmd:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Surgery"
msgstr "Kirurgia"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_surgery.Rmd:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "`r dR$numberOfSurgicalDepartments` of the partner departments in this dataset (`r dR$proportionOfSurgicalDepartments`) recorded a total of `r dR$numberOfSurgicalProcedures` surgical procedures performed on `r dR$numberOfSurgicalPatients` neonates, resulting in an average number of `r dR$numberOfSurgicalProceduresPerPatient` operations per surgical patient during the surveillance period.\n"
msgstr "`r dR$numberOfSurgicalDepartments` partnerosakonnast selles andmekogus (`r dR$proportionOfSurgicalDepartments` %) registreerisid kokku `r dR$numberOfSurgicalProcedures` kirurgilist protseduuri, mis tehti `r dR$numberOfSurgicalPatients` vastsündinule, mis tähendab keskmiselt `r dR$numberOfSurgicalProceduresPerPatient` operatsiooni kirurgilise patsiendi kohta järelevalveperioodi jooksul.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: reports/Reference-Report/content/_surgery.Rmd:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Due to the low number of surgical site infections in this dataset (n = `r dR$numberOfSurgicalSiteInfections`) we are not currently calculating their infection rates, but @tbl-surgical-procedure-rates provides an overview of the categories of procedures performed on neonates.\n"
msgstr "Kuna selles andmekogus on kirurgiliste infektsioonide arv väike (n = `r dR$numberOfSurgicalSiteInfections`), ei arvuta me praegu nende infektsioonimäärasid, kuid @tbl-surgical-procedure-rates on esitatud ülevaade vastsündinutele tehtud protseduuride kategooriatest.\n"
